1. new Image('gray') converts to 32 bit (and does it wrong)
2. a = new Image('rgb', new Buffer('aaa'), 1, 1)
  b = new Image('rgb', new Buffer('\x01\x02\x03'), 1, 1)
  b.subtract(a).toBuffer() -> <Buffer 9f a0 a2>
  expected <Buffer 0 0 0>, it is supposed to clip channel-wise!
  
  (works for grayscale!)
3. new Image().subtract(new Image()) segfaults
